						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near the road side close to the gate of the model village.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 10th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It records the self-immolation of Kasavāḍa Gaṅga consequent on the death of (his master) Pallaya Arumurāja and registers a gift of 12 <hi rend="italic">maṟutus</hi> of land to his family.</p>						

						</summary>
